manhattan district attorney robert morgenthau said tuesday that a former employee of abrams' office had been arrested and charged with stealing and disclosing a transcript of testimony taken before the dutchess county grand jury investigating the attack on tawana brawley
abrams was appointed by gov. mario cuomo as a special prosecutor to investigate the case
miss brawley, 16, was found on nov. 28 in wappingers falls after having disappeared for four days. she was wrapped in a plastic garbage bag and covered with feces, with ``kkk'' and ``nigger'' scrawled on her body
on the advice of her attorneys, she has not cooperated with investigators since shortly after the attack
