abrams said the arrest will not affect the investigation, which continues monday when a special state grand jury is to be empaneled in poughkeepsie
samuel evans, 49, was employed as the senior printing machine operator in abrams' office until his resignation on feb. 5. he allegedly stole the brawley transcript before he left the job
evans, of new york city, surrendered to the district attorney's office on tuesday
according to morgenthau, evans gave the transcript to an unidentified person on feb. 18. that person notified the district attorney's office
evans is charged with fourth-degree grand larceny, which carries a maximum penalty of four years in prison upon conviction
the material did not go beyond evans and the informant, and no other document relating to the case was stolen, abrams said
