the news tribune, woodbridge, n.j., on the verdict in the amtrak crash:
sixteen people died, scores were injured, and tens of millions of dollars worth of damage was done when a conrail engineer ran his locomotive through a stop sign and plowed into an amtrak passenger train. the engineer tested positive for marijuana use
after he pleaded guilty to one count of manslaughter, he was given a maximum sentence of five years in jail and a $1,000 fine
unless he had been hiding in a cave, rick gates knew what marijuana could do to the senses. gates also had to know the damage a misguided train could cause
so what was the message? sixteen dead passengers equals five years maximum, which doesn't sound like much of a deterrent to us
