the duluth (minn.) news-tribune on the 1990 census:
let's conduct a census and count everybody but swedes ... or maybe irish ... or americans who migrate with the seasons ... or some other identifiable population group
why do that? to fix the outcome, silly. what other reason could there be?
a coalition of congressional members wants to do that in 1990 when the constitution says the country must conduct a decennial head count
about 40 house members want to count everyone but illegal aliens and will sue the census bureau to force the exclusion. it is estimated there are about 2 million illegal aliens in the united states
why do these members of congress want to ignore illegal aliens? to fix the outcome of the 1990 census, of course
the national head count is used to distribute seats in the house of representatives, and they fear aliens will cause unfair shifts from one state to another
to their credit, census officials say they read the constitution to say everyone must be counted (``the whole number of persons'')
of course, everyone should be included
