sen. hainon miller of greenvill introduced the bill monday at the urging of mary jo ayres of leland, who wants to add the chocolate dessert to the list of state-sanctioned m-words so she can help her students pronounce the consonant
if you think about it, it never occurred to me before, but we have `mississippi' _ it starts with an `m.' mmm-mmm-mmm-mmm,'' miller said
and the official state bird is the m-m-mocking bird,'' he said, ``and the official flower is the m-m-m-magnolia.''
and what would one eat with mud cake? the official state drink _ m-m-milk, of course
ewing oil is selling the southern cross ranch, where scenes for the television show ``dallas'' have been shot
the seller is the real ewing oil of dallas, not the nasty, power-hungry outfit run by j.r. ewing on the cbs nighttime serial
on the show, the ewings' ranch is supposed to be in san angelo in west texas. in real life, it's a breeding ranch in forney, 20 miles east of dallas
the 455-acre ranch features a two-story spanish-style home atop a hill, a swimming pool, a gazebo, a guest house, a foreman's house, stables and stock tanks
harry james, one of the principal owners of ewing oil, gave the ranch to the company as equity, and it was recently appraised at $61.5 million, the company said
tim bell, ewing oil's chief executive officer, said the ranch is not generating revenue for the company. ``it has nothing to do with the rise and fall of oil prices. we're just not in the ranching business,'' bell said
he said the ranch has not been used in the filming of ``dallas'' for several years
melvin giller, president of nationwide auction co., said he's unsure what the ranch will bring on the auction block march 12, but has received more than 500 calls since it was advertised
