the family has always held jimmy on a pedestal so high that this is a total shock to us,'' gilley said tuesday in an interview with the nashville banner
we were saddened when he went on television and said he had a personal problem and had made a mistake,'' gilley said from houston. ``but i will have to say it takes a very strong man to say what he did.''
on sunday, swaggart confessed to an unspecified sin before 7,500 people at his family worship center in baton rouge, la
