total crude oil runs to stills averaged 12,695,000 barrels daily during the week ended friday, feb. 19, the american petroleum institute reported wednesday. this compared with 12,739,000 barrels daily in the previous week and 12,199,000 barrels daily a year ago
crude runs east of california averaged 10,243,000 barrels daily compared with 10,330,000 the previous week and 9,749,000 a year ago
motor gasoline production for the latest week amounted to 6,760,000 barrels a day, compared with 6,641,000 barrels a day in the previous week and 6,406,000 a day a year ago
east of california motor gasoline production was 5,677,000 a day compared with 5,552,000 a day last week and 5,300,000 a day a year ago
motor gasoline stocks at the end of the latest week were 240,493,000 barrels, versus 236,560,000 a week earlier and 252,947,000 a year ago
east of california motor gasoline stocks totaled 207,918,000 barrels, compared with 203,396,000 in the previous week and 221,181,000 barrels last year
daily average gross crude oil and lease condensate production for the week ended friday was 8,182,000 barrels compared with 8,320,000 last year
crude oil stocks totaled 333,084,000 barrels at the close of last week, against 334,964,000 a week previous and 328,680,000 a year ago
east of california crude stocks amounted to 250,753,000 barrels, compared with 251,609,000 a week earlier
